<p></span><font face="Arial"><span style="font-size:13pt"><b>Incoming Orders - Quotation</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></p>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">This function can be used to send Quotation for the selected Incoming Customer Order.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Click on <b>+Upload </b>button to upload the Quotation and the relevant documents. On clicking the 
<b>+Upload </b>button, a standard Windows <b>File Open</b> dialog box opens, allowing you to choose the 
file(in this case a Quotation) that has been already created. Click on <b>Open </b>to upload the selected 
document for the Current Customer Order.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Use the <b>Notes </b>Section to provide any specific notes pertaining to this Order. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Click on <b>Send</b> to send the Quotation details to the Customer. The Customer can see this 
Quotation once he has logged on to the Bixera Application. The Quotation appears as an 
<b>Incoming </b>Email in the top right hand corner of his Bixera Application.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">If you do not wish to <b>Send </b>the Quotation and ignore the details provided in this screen, simply 
Click<b>&#160;</b> on the <b>Close Button.</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
